    "contents": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"install-ruby-gems-into-virtualenv\">\n<h1>Install Ruby gems into&nbsp;virtualenv</h1>\n<p>You are a Python developer and every time you have to install a Ruby gem you\nthrow up in your mouth a little. Wouldn&#8217;t it be nice if you could install Ruby\ngems into your virtualenv? Yeah, it&nbsp;would.</p>\n<p>Stick this in your virtualenv&#8217;s <tt class=\"docutils literal\">postactivate</tt> script:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span class=\"nb\">export </span><span class=\"nv\">GEM_HOME</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;</span><span class=\"nv\">$VIRTUAL_ENV</span><span class=\"s2\">/gems&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">export </span><span class=\"nv\">GEM_PATH</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">&quot;&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">export </span><span class=\"nv\"><span class=\"caps\">PATH</span></span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"nv\">$<span class=\"caps\">PATH</span></span>:<span class=\"s2\">&quot;</span><span class=\"nv\">$GEM_HOME</span><span class=\"s2\">/bin&quot;</span>\n</pre></div>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! You&#8217;re welcome.&nbsp;:)</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"credit\">\n<h2>Credit</h2>\n<p>Give credit where credit is due. I stole this idea from <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"http://twitter.com/idangazit\">Idan Gazit</a> and\nmade it&nbsp;better.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n", 
